<item>
            <title>[LU-15552] Interop: sanity-flr test 0d fails with &apos;exceeded maximum mirror count returns 16 not ERANGE(34)&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15552</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity-flr test_0d started failing on February 1, 2022 with &apos;exceeded maximum mirror count returns 16 not ERANGE(34)&apos; with2.12.7 servers and 2.14.57.72 clients; see &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/553bed32-113b-4dff-b91c-f459cadefe67&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/553bed32-113b-4dff-b91c-f459cadefe67&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the suite log, we see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity-flr test 0d: lfs mirror extend with -N option == 12:26:44 (1643718404)
CMD: trevis-59vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param -n obdfilter.lustre-OST*.lfsck_verify_pfid=1
CMD: trevis-59vm3 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param -n obdfilter.lustre-OST*.lfsck_verify_pfid=0
 sanity-flr test_0d: @@@@@@ FAIL: exceeded maximum mirror count returns 16 not ERANGE(34) 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6386:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity-flr.sh:536:test_0d()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15268&quot; title=&quot;lfs mirror extend error propagation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15268&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15268&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &#8216;mdt: reveal the real intent close error code&#8217; , &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/45636&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/45636&lt;/a&gt;, modified this test to check the return code that leads to this failure. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
